<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-04T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-04T07:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4070: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                            Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-04T09:00:00-03:00">September 4, 1934—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>204. Brazilian Minister in La Paz has been instructed by telegraph to
                                obtain from the Bolivian Minister for Foreign Affairs before
                                September 7th, on which date the League Committee meets,<note n="25" xml:id="d242fn25">See <ref target="#pg_32">pp. 32</ref>
                                    ff.</note> a definite statement as to Bolivian claims.</p>
                            <p>Same telegram instructs Minister to suggest to Bolivian Minister for
                                Foreign Affairs that Bolivia request the League to postpone action
                                in connection with the application of article No. 15.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>